+==== CSRs
+
+[[ACE-CSR-aceiobuftop]]
+===== `aceiobuftop`
+
+{empty}
+(((CSR, `aceiobuftop`)))
+`aceiobuftop` is an XLEN-bit URW CSR that marks the upper bound in bits of the buffer range used by `ace.input` and `ace.output`.
+Together with `acestart`, it defines the active transfer window.
+
+The constraints `acestart` {le} `aceiobuftop` {le} `aceiobuflen` must hold.
+Violating either bound raises an illegal instruction exception.
+Modifying `aceiobuftop` does not modify buffer contents.
+
+NOTE: `aceiobuftop` enables per-operation length adjustments without the need to reconfigure the ACEIOBUF using `aceiobuflen`, which can be expensive due to the fact that it clears the buffer and may lead to internal garbage collection.
+This can be used similarly to the reconfiguration of `VL*SEW` to provide an partial “last block” or to supply a short IV/nonce to cryptographic algorithms.
+
+Using a alternative sequence for `ace.exec` or `ace.setst` for any Form with an input or output
+when `aceiobuftop` − `acestart` is zero (and `aceiobuflen` nonzero) will result in no operation being performed.
+
+Using ACEIOBUF when `aceiobuftop` − `acestart` is an invalid length raises an illegal instruction exception.
+
+Since context switching code saves and restores the contents of the ACEIOBUF up to `aceiobuflen`, the contents between `aceiobuftop` and `aceiobuflen` are preserved.
+
+// ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
+
+[[ACE-CSR-aceiobuflen]]
+===== `aceiobuflen`
+
+{empty}
+(((CSR, `aceiobuflen`)))
+`aceiobuflen` is an XLEN-bit URW CSR that programs the ACEIOBUF length in bits for use by `ace.input` and `ace.output`.
+Writing this register-even when re-writing the current value-also zeroes the buffer and sets `aceiobuftop` to the same length and `acestart` to zero.
+
+When `aceiobuflen` is zero, the ACEIOBUF is _unconfigured_.
+Attempting to execute an operation that expects an input or an output in the ACEIOBUF while the latter is unconfigured raises exception `ace_exc_buf_unconf`.
+
+Writing a value larger than `acemaxiobuflen` raises exception `ace_exc_out_of_mem`.
+
+[NOTE]
+====
+As per the Privileged Architecture, the dirtiness of the ACEIOBUF is not tracked except as part of the entire ACE state in `*status`.
+Context switching code is expected to save and restore the contents of the ACEIOBUF up to `aceiobuflen`.
+We recommend software to set `aceiobuflen` to zero once the contents of the ACEIOBUF are no longer needed.
+Context switching code can use this information to avoid unnecessary save and restore of ACEIOBUF contents.
+====
+
+// ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
+
+[[ACE-CSR-acemaxiobuflen]]
+===== `acemaxiobuflen`
+
+{empty}
+(((CSR, `acemaxiobuflen`)))
+`acemaxiobuflen` is an XLEN-bit RO CSR that reports the maximum configurable length of the ACEIOBUF.
+
